title: Commission Regulation (EC) No 172/2009 of 4 March 2009 fixing the import duties applicable to certain husked rice from 5 March 2009
header:
5.3.2009 EN Official Journal of the European Union L 61/10
COMMISSION REGULATION (EC) No 172/2009
of 4 March 2009
fixing the import duties applicable to certain husked rice from 5 March 2009
THE COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES
recitals:
,
Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community,
Having regard to Council Regulation (EC) No 1234/2007 of 22 October 2007 establishing a common organisation of agricultural markets and on specific provisions for certain agricultural products (Single CMO Regulation) (1), and in particular Article 137 thereof,
Whereas:
(1) Based on the information provided by the competent authorities, the Commission notes that import licences for husked rice falling within CN code 1006 20, other than import licences for basmati rice, were issued in respect of 221 765 tonnes for the period from 1 September 2008 to 28 February 2009. The import duty for husked rice falling within CN code 1006 20 other than basmati rice should therefore be adjusted.
(2) The applicable duty must be fixed within 10 days of the end of the period mentioned above. This Regulation should therefore come into force immediately,
main_body: The import duty for husked rice falling within CN code 1006 20 shall be EUR 42,5 per tonne.

This Regulation shall enter into force on the day of its publication in the Official Journal of the European Union.
This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States.
attachments:
Done at Brussels, 4 March 2009.
For the Commission
Jean-Luc DEMARTY
Director-General for Agriculture and Rural Development
(1)  OJ L 299, 16.11.2007, p. 1.
